Name: Misbelief
Author: Dan Ariely
Written by Dan Ariely, this books investigates how rational people can end up believing irrational concepts. The book revolves around misbelief experienced by the author himself, and explains in detail about the things he found while investigating.
Reccomended?
Yes. This is not only a good book to study, it is also a very good book that you can read in spare time. I read it and I loved it. If you want to study anything related to complex mental structures about belief and cognition, this would definitely be a go-to book. Keep in mind that however good this book is, its content is still limited, and if you want to conduct research, additional literature review is reccomended.
